00:00:17.810 --> 00:00:19.110
I really liked the book.

00:00:19.110 --> 00:00:21.470
I gave it a positive review.

00:00:21.470 --> 00:00:24.560
So did everyone else in the world.

00:00:24.560 --> 00:00:28.330
The New York Times review
called Claire Messud a novelist

00:00:28.330 --> 00:00:30.900
of unnerving talent.

00:00:30.900 --> 00:00:35.470
The book was widely celebrated,
named one of the Times's best books

00:00:35.470 --> 00:00:39.130
of the year, 10 best books of
the year, and was long listed

00:00:39.130 --> 00:00:41.270
for The Man Booker Prize.

00:00:41.270 --> 00:00:45.570
Claire Messud's new book,
The Burning Girl, is,

00:00:45.570 --> 00:00:51.850
according to NPR's review, now I'm
quoting, a subversive commentary

00:00:51.850 --> 00:00:53.850
on the stories we tell about women

00:00:53.850 --> 00:00:57.800
and the way those stories
circumscribe our lives.

00:00:57.800 --> 00:00:59.920 position:56%
